def: Double; duplicate; multiplied by two; as, a twofold nature; atwofold sense; a twofold argument.
Placed in a pulpit. [R.]Sit . . . at the feet of a pulpited divine. Milton.
A piece of ground used for recreation; as, the playground of aschool.
To destroy the aggregation of; to separate into componentparts, as an aggregate mass.
The history or description of the sacred writings or of sacredpersons; a narrative of the lives of the saints; a catalogue ofsaints. J. H. Newman.
Chief physician; -- a term applied, on the continent of Europe,to the first or body physician of princes and to the first physicianof some cities. P. Cyc.
A species of fern (Lomaria borealis), growing in Europe andNorthwestern America.
